                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>No one should face cancer alone, which is why AbbVie has enlisted a full suite of oncology care resources to help guide its U.S.-based employees and their family members through every phase of the cancer journey.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>AbbVie has partnered with a specialized vendor to offer enhanced oncology benefits through a personalized healthcare app. Examples of no-cost services provided by the app include cancer screening reminders that aid in prevention and early detection. It also incorporates treatment navigation to coordinate expert opinions from National Cancer Institute-designated centers.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Whether it's understanding available benefits, navigating health care complexities or identifying oncology providers, AbbVie is providing personalized help to employees navigating this challenging time, allowing its people to focus on what truly matters to them and their loved ones.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy_5187>
                            <quote
                                cq:styleIds="[1000000000000]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2024-04-30T15:05:49.749-04:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-03T17:01:27.404-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/quote"
                                attributionName="Lesli Marasco,"
                                attributionTitle=" VP, Global Benefits and Well-being, AbbVie"
                                bgImageModifiers="resMode=sharp2&amp;op_sharpen=1"
                                fileReference="/content/dam/abbvie-com2/images/stories/transforming-cancer-care-from-the-inside-out/Lesli-Marasco-headshot.jpg"
                                imageModifiers="resMode=sharp2&amp;op_sharpen=1"
                                quote="It's about more than just benefits; it's about standing together, empowering our people and making a real difference in their lives."
                                quoteType="regular"
                                textSize="h0"/>
                            <container4_copy_5187_1355220684
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-06T09:56:18.886-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>&amp;quot;By listening closely to our employees’ needs and crafting personalized resources, we're not just offering assistance: We're showing our commitment to each individual's journey. It's about more than just benefits; it's about standing together, empowering our people and making a real difference in their lives” says Lesli Marasco, vice president, global benefits and well-being, AbbVie.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>As a global leader in oncology, AbbVie sits at the intersection of where compassion meets innovation in the fight against cancer. And Lisa Moreno knows firsthand why this work matters.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“I cannot imagine going through what I did without having the AbbVie team in my corner,” she says. “It is the small things that companies can do to support their employees that truly make a difference.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>References&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ol>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Key Stats for Pancreatic Cancer. (2024). American Cancer Society. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cancer.org/cancer/types/pancreatic-cancer/about/key-statistics.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>https://www.cancer.org/cancer/types/pancreatic-cancer/about/key-statistics.html&lt;/a>. Accessed April 19, 2024.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Cancer Stat Facts: Cancer of Any Site. (2020). National Cancer Institute Surveillance, Epidemiology, and End Results Program.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;a href=&quot;https://seer.cancer.gov/statfacts/html/all.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>https://seer.cancer.gov/statfacts/html/all.html&lt;/a>. Accessed March 18, 2024.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Work Motivation, Disclosure &amp;amp; Need for Support. (2023). Cancer and Careers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cancerandcareers.org/newsfeed/research/posts/2023/12/2023-cancer-and-careers-the-ha&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>https://www.cancerandcareers.org/newsfeed/research/posts/2023/12/2023-cancer-and-careers-the-ha&lt;/a>. Accessed March 18, 2024.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ol>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>Media inquiries:&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa; &lt;/b>&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:abbviemediarelations@abbvie.com&quot;>abbviemediarelations@abbvie.com&lt;/a>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy_5187_1355220684>
                        </par_12>
